PHASE 6 BEHAVIOR VERIFIED
- Surviving squads physically return to their base, remain in state and enter RECOVERING then READY status.
- Major bases naturally restore all squad types to full HP at 0.6% maximum HP per second with a 45-second reorganization requirement.
- Civilization Lv.1 unlocks treatment facilities at major bases and simple aid stations at field bases, one matching facility per base.
- Treatment Tiers 1–4 heal at 1.2%, 1.6%, 2.1% and 2.7% maximum HP per second and reduce reorganization to 30, 24, 18 and 12 seconds.
- Treatment Tiers 3–4 process two formations at once; excess formations remain in a deterministic queue without losing state.
- Simple bases reorganize assault and skirmisher squads without natural healing. A simple aid station heals them to a 70% HP ceiling.
- Legacy heavy formations at a simple base remain recoverable as data but receive no field healing.
- A ready formation of the same type redeploys without a new formation cost and preserves its identity. Replacing it with a different type charges the full normal cost.
- Recovering and ready formations reject tactical movement commands and are controlled through the deployment screen.
- Destroying a simple base during recovery sends its formation by road to the nearest reachable established major base; no teleport or silent deletion is used.
- Ruined or disabled treatment facilities immediately stop contributing and the base falls back to its natural recovery profile.
- Recovery status, target HP, treatment source, queue state and reorganization time survive save/restore.
- Base command, deployment, squad detail, construction and civilization interfaces expose the relevant recovery state and values.

ISSUES FOUND AND CORRECTED
1. Existing withdrawal regression expected a returned squad to be deleted. It now verifies transition into recovery at the origin.
2. Recovery at a destroyed simple base could remain frozen indefinitely. The formation now evacuates along a valid road route to the nearest major base.
3. Ready and recovering squads could still be addressed through low-level tactical-order functions. Those commands are now explicitly rejected.
4. Base command counted recovering and ready garrisons as active deployments. It now separates active, recovering and ready counts.
5. Simple-base UI still claimed only assault squads were allowed after skirmishers were introduced in v0.26.0. The text now states assault/skirmisher deployment.
6. The civilization tier catalog omitted the new treatment and aid lines. Both are now displayed with their unlock levels.
7. Passive treatment buildings were still considered by route-support hazard scanning. Medical, aid, repair and survey support facilities are excluded from attack-range route scoring.

